  "description": "Standardize News Card Design Across Application\n\nUpdate the news card component on the homepage to match the superior design and layout currently used on the dedicated news page.\n\nRequirements:\n- Audit both card implementations to identify specific visual and structural differences\n- Apply the news page card styling (colors, spacing, typography, shadows, borders) to the homepage card\n- Ensure consistent card dimensions, image aspect ratios, and content alignment\n- Match interaction states (hover effects, click behavior, focus states)\n- Verify responsive behavior matches across both locations\n- Consolidate duplicate code by creating a shared card component if implementations are separate\n- Test appearance across different viewport sizes and browsers\n- Ensure no regression in functionality (links, accessibility, performance)\n\nSuccess criteria:\n- Homepage news cards are visually indistinguishable from news page cards\n- Both cards use the same component or styling system\n- No visual inconsistencies across breakpoints",
